        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-04-22T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-04-22T05:00:00-05:00" n="88" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d88">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4–2247: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-04-22T19:00:00+09:00">April 22, 1947—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 23—4:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>874. RefEmbtel 861, April 21, 4 p.m.<note n="67" xml:id="d88fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> Official Central News Agency has announced that on April 21
                    the Central Executive Committee of the Kuomintang decided to abrogate that
                    provision in article 15 of the organic law of the National Govt providing for
                    presidential responsibility to the Kuomintang.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
